1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with problems related to geometric Traveling Salesman Problem and automatic tool path generation, which are typical topics in computational geometry.
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes efficient approximation algorithms for several versions of the problem, which is a core topic in data structures and algorithms.
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper proves the NP-completeness of minimum-turn milling, which is a typical topic in discrete mathematics.
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper mentions automatic inspection systems, which are related to robotics and automation.
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper deals with the complexity of the problem and proves its NP-completeness, which is a typical topic in computational complexity.
